article.headline: Tennessee Tech 81, Kennesaw State 68
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Kevin Murphy scored 21 points and had 10 rebounds to lead Tennessee Tech to an 81-68 victory over Kennesaw State on Thursday in the Las Vegas Classic. Jud Dillard had 16 points and nine rebounds for the Golden Eagles (7-5), who shot 59 percent and converted 7 of 13 3-pointers. Liam McMorrow added 15 points and seven rebounds and Zach Bailey had 13 points for the Golden Eagles, who will play Bethune-Cookman in the final round Friday. Markeith Cummings led Kennesaw State (2-9) with a season-high 27 points. Spencer Dixon added 22 points and six assists for the Owls, who will face Texas A&M-Corpus Christi on Friday. After leading 46-35 at halftime, Tennessee Tech increased the gap to 16 with 14:54 left. The Owls never got closer than six points the rest of the way.
